<p>which, in its lack of military appearances, was far better than Tidworth which I also occasionally visited.<br/>After about a fortnight at Perham we left one Friday morning for Parkhouse &amp; arrived here to find the tone &amp; personel of the camp almost entirely changed.  Major Johnson had given place to Major Kennedy, a straighter &amp; more decent chap Craig was still W.O. but the other N.C.O's were new men.<br/>A great number of war babys &ndash; under aged boys culled from the battalions, &amp; awaiting the fulfilment of age to go overseas with A.M.C. &ndash; were in the camp.</p>
